      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get the balance thing, but it feels like people use \"fiscal responsibility\" as an excuse to ignore the actual human cost. if a country is trillions in debt but still has massive inequality, isn't the \"stable\" economy actually kind of a failure? shouldn't the priority always be the people living in it right now?",
